  <steps>
    <step num="0">In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, salt, and pepper. </step>
    <step num="1">In a ramekin, spread two-thirds of the beef patty evenly along the bottom and the sides. </step>
    <step num="2">Place half the diced onion and provolone in the well. </step>
    <step num="3">Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C). </step>
    <step num="4">Place the rest of beef patty on top and pat to flatten. </step>
    <step num="5">Place the ramekin on a baking sheet along with a sesame bun, face down. </step>
    <step num="6">Bake for 25 minutes. </step>
    <step num="7">Assemble the burger with the sesame bun, lettuce, and the rest of the onion. </step>
    <step num="8">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
